### Code

```Rust
trait MyTrait {}
struct ImT1 {}
impl MyTrait for ImT1 {}
struct ImT2 {}
impl MyTrait for ImT2 {}
pub struct MyStruct {
  imt1: ImT1,
  imt2: ImT2,
}

impl MyStruct {
  pub fn mytrait_array_mut(&mut self) -> &[&dyn MyTrait] {
    [
      self.imt1,
      self.imt2,
    ]
  }  
}
```


### Current output

```Shell
error[E0308]: mismatched types
  --> src/main.rs:16:7
   |
16 |       self.imt2,
   |       ^^^^^^^^^ expected `ImT1`, found `ImT2`

For more information about this error, try `rustc --explain E0308`.
```


### Desired output

```Shell
What should the suggested output be? Leaving it blank and hoping for good recommendations.
```


### Rationale and extra context

This error message is WORSE than a segfault because it is misleading. It gives the wrong message. At least segfaults tell you that there was an illegal memory operation.

